cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the problem of detecting texts in natural images, which is a common task in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also makes use of machine learning techniques, specifically supervised Support Vector Machines (SVM), which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves image processing and probabilistic frameworks, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions testing on the ICDAR 10 dataset and other images available on the internet, indicating that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
